            <bug_when>2011-12-14 13:50:18 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>If a right click on a widget is simulated using qxClick or qxClickAt, the &quot;click&quot; event on the widget does not fire (&quot;contextmenu&quot; works). &quot;click&quot; fires on a manual click and the simulated action should cause the same behavior.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>29643</commentid>
            <who name="Daniel Wagner">daniel.wagner</who>
            <bug_when>2012-06-01 15:15:52 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>Only Firefox fires a &quot;click&quot; event on the document (but not on the target element) on right click. Since this is browser-specific behavior, I don&#39;t think we need to simulate it.</thetext>
